{
  "id": "ALAS2023-2026-1454",
  "title": "Amazon Linux 2023 - ALAS2023-2026-1454: Important priority package update for freerdp",
  "issued": {
    "date": "2026-03-02 09:00:00"
  },
  "updated": {
    "date": "2026-03-05 15:47:00"
  },
  "severity": "Important",
  "description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux 2023 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2026-24684:\n\tClient side issue with FreeRDP\n\nCVE-2026-24683:\n\tClient side issue with FreeRDP\n\nCVE-2026-24682:\n\tClient side issue with FreeRDP\n\nCVE-2026-24681:\n\tClient side issue with FreeRDP\n\nCVE-2026-24680:\n\tClient side issue with FreeRDP\n\nCVE-2026-24679:\n\tClient side issue with FreeRDP\n\nCVE-2026-24678:\n\tClient side issue with FreeRDP\n\nCVE-2026-24677:\n\tClient side issue with FreeRDP\n\nCVE-2026-24676:\n\tClient side issue with FreeRDP\n\nCVE-2026-24675:\n\tClient side issue with FreeRDP\n\nCVE-2026-24491:\n\tClient side issue with FreeRDP\n\nCVE-2026-23948:\n\tFreeRDP is a free implementation of the Remote Desktop Protocol. Prior to 3.22.0, a NULL pointer dereference vulnerability in rdp_write_logon_info_v2() allows a malicious RDP server to crash FreeRDP proxy by sending a specially crafted LogonInfoV2 PDU with cbDomain=0 or cbUserName=0. This vulnerability is fixed in 3.22.0.\n",
